								<a name="content"></a><p class="lead"><strong>Recall from Word Processing, that you can choose the font as well as effects for your document. You have this same ability in the spreadsheets program.  </strong></p class="lead">




<p>There are many options from which to choose. In selecting the font, recall that you choose not only the font but also the font size. Default font size is usually a 10 or 12.</p>

<p>You also have many of the same options for effects on text or numeric data, like <strong>bold</strong>, <i>italics</i>, and <u>underline</u>.</p> 

<p>In order change the font, font size, or effects, you can either access the <strong>Format Cells Box</strong> or you can use the toolbar (Classic Excel) or ribbon (Excel 2007-20XX). Since we have explored the Format Cells Box, let's use the toolbar and ribbon.</p>

<p>You must first select the range of cells where you want to make changes. When they are highlighted, use the toolbar to choose the font, font size and text effects you want.</p>

